The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, March 1: Public sector oil firms today cut aviation turbine fuel prices by less than a percentage point after raising it twice in the last two months. Jet fuel price for domestic airlines in Delhi was cut by Rs 233.63 per kilolitre to Rs 34,995.36, while the decrease in Mumbai was Rs 256.88 per kl to Rs 35,957.79, industry sources said.

 New Delhi, March 1: The Prime Minister?s investment commission today mooted labour reforms, speeding up of infrastructure development and removing bureaucratic hurdles to improve the investment climate in the country. 

 Mumbai, March 1: Reliance Natural Resources Ltd was listed at Rs 17.50 on the stock exchanges today. The RNRL shares on the Bombay Stock Exchange touched a high of Rs 30. Reliance Communication Ventures has also filed papers with stock exchanges for listing.

 Calcutta, March 1: A petition seeking speedy enquiry and trial of the criminal complaint case against R.S. Lodha and his three associates was moved before a city court today by complainant R.P. Pansari in connection with the Rs 5000 crore assets of MP Birla group.

 New Delhi, March 1: Finance minister P. Chidambram will meet Prime Minister Manmohan Singh and petroleum minister Murli Deora soon to discuss bailout of oil companies.




